Reasoning: 
1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes an algorithm for robust time series analysis using recent advances in robust regression and hard-thresholding methods. This falls under the domain of machine learning and hence, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category.
2. cs.ST (Statistics): Time series analysis is a sub-field of statistics and the paper deals with robust time series analysis. Hence, cs.ST is also a likely sub-category.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes an algorithm for robust time series analysis which can be considered as a sub-field of artificial intelligence. Hence, cs.AI is also a likely sub-category.
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes an efficient algorithm for robust time series analysis which involves estimating the corrupted set of points and the model parameters alternately. This falls under the domain of data structures and algorithms and hence, cs.DS is also a likely sub-category.
5. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the problem of robust time series analysis under the standard auto-regressive (AR) time series model in the presence of arbitrary outliers. This involves dealing with noise and information loss, which falls under the domain of information theory. Hence, cs.IT is also a likely sub-category.
